           <strong>üáªüá≥ Vietnam - Hosts Macron.</strong> France signed over $10B in agreements with Vietnam, including Airbus aircraft, defense cooperation, and space technology. These agreements enhance France‚Äôs influence amid US tariff threats and Vietnam‚Äôs efforts to balance its relations with Western powers. This comes amid Vietnam‚Äôs efforts to counter growing Chinese assertiveness in the region (<a style="text-decoration: none; border-bottom: 2px solid  #06266D; color: black;" href="https://link.geopoliticalsummary.com/gs-27-may-25-worldwide-7-balancing-act" target="_blank">balancing measures</a>).
          </p>
          <p style="font-size:16px;line-height:1.5;padding-bottom:6px;">
           <strong>üá™üá∫ EU - Trump delays tariffs.</strong>  Trump has agreed to delay a threatened 50% tariff on the European Union until July 9, following a "very nice call" with EU Commission President Ursula von der Leyen. The pause aims to allow more time for negotiations. Markets reacted positively, though concerns remain about Trump‚Äôs volatile trade approach and global economic impact (<a style="text-decoration: none; border-bottom: 2px solid  #06266D; color: black;" href="https://link.geopoliticalsummary.com/gs-27-may-25-worldwide-8-the-very-nice-call" target="_blank">the very nice call</a>).
          </p>
          <p style="font-size:16px;line-height:1.5;padding-bottom:6px;">
           <strong>üá∫üá≤ USA - Trump mad at Putin.</strong> Donald Trump sharply criticized Vladimir Putin as ‚Äúabsolutely crazy‚Äù after Russia launched its deadliest aerial assault on Ukraine in three years. Despite previously praising Putin, Trump condemned the attacks as senseless and signaled possible sanctions. In response, the Kremlin asserted that Trump was showing signs of "emotional overload" (<a style="text-decoration: none; border-bottom: 2px solid  #06266D; color: black;" href="https://link.geopoliticalsummary.com/gs-27-may-25-worldwide-9-frustrations-grow" target="_blank">frustrations grow</a>). 
