           Chancellor Friedrich Merz is becoming increasingly frustrated with Israel‚Äôs military campaign in Gaza, stating he "no longer understands" its goals. He criticizes the suffering inflicted on civilians and urges actions that allies can support. His comments reflect a shift among Western leaders, as pressure mounts on Israel to scale back its offensive and allow greater humanitarian aid permits to the Strip (<a style="text-decoration: none; border-bottom: 2px solid  #06266D; color: black;" href="https://link.geopoliticalsummary.com/gs-27-may-25-worldwide-10-questions-on-strategy" target="_blank">questions on strategy</a>).
